PrecisRegulations Amending the BENZENE IN GASOLINE REGULATIONS by (a) allowing suppliers to apply for temporary alternative limits on the benzene content of gasoline, (b) exempting gasoline stored in the north for emergencies from the lower benzene requirements, and (c) adopting the National Standard of Canada method CAN/CGSB-3.0 No. 16.1-98 as the official method of determining the sulphur content of gasoline.
